HEADWORD: Pheon
<hw>Phe"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from Old
French.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A bearing representing the head of
a dart or javelin, with long barbs which are engrailed on the inner
edge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

